sibility": 0.85, "pathway_coherence": 0.83, "environmental_progression": 0.81, "target_achievement": 0.9, "overall_confidence": 0.84, "feedback": "As a short endpoint route from proline aminonitrile to proline, this pathway is chemically plausible and consistent with classic aminonitrile hydrolysis logic. It is necessarily incomplete as a standalone origin route because it assumes access to proline aminonitrile, but as a route variant it works well.", "approved": true, "problematic_reactions": [], "suggestions": ["Frame this explicitly as a terminal conversion module rather than a full de novo pathway", "Specify hydrolysis conditions and possible mineral or evaporative assistance for concentration", "Note likely racemic outcome"]}, {"pathway_id": "P7", "reaction_scores": {"rxn_011": 0.88, "rxn_012": 0.34}, "chemical_feasibility": 0.5, "pathway_coherence": 0.58, "environmental_progression": 0.63, "target_achievement": 0.55, "overall_confidence": 0.5, "feedback": "HCN oligomerization to DAMN is well supported, but the direct conversion of DAMN-derived polymers to proline in a single hydrolysis/thermal step is too underspecified. The literature supports proline appearing among hydrolysis products of HCN polymers under some conditions, but not as a clean direct DAMN -> proline transformation. This pathway is therefore only weakly supported and overly compressed.", "approved": false, "problematic_reactions": ["rxn_012"], "suggestions": ["Insert hydantoin or related HCN polymer intermediates supported by the literature", "Treat proline as a minor distribution product from polymer hydrolysis rather than a defined sole output", "Lower confidence claims and mark the route as speculative"]}, {"pathway_id": "P8", "reaction_scores": {"rxn_011": 0.88, "rxn_012": 0.34}, "chemical_feasibility": 0.49, "pathway_coherence": 0.56, "environmental_progression": 0.66, "target_achievement": 0.55, "overall_confidence": 0.49, "feedback": "This concentrated HCN pool variant inherits the same